# Instruction

This file is a navigation map for iterative work on the Event Processing
Engine. It is not an implementation spec and it must not duplicate details that
already live in the focused `docs/` files.

Use this file first to decide what to read next. Read detailed docs only for the
current coding context.

## How To Work

1. Start from the current user request.
2. Identify the relevant context below.
3. Open only the referenced detailed docs.
4. Inspect the existing code for that slice.
5. Implement one small, working change.
6. Verify with the narrowest useful test or smoke check.

Avoid re-reading the whole documentation set unless the task explicitly asks for
a broad review.

## Mental Model

This project is an order event processing engine. At a high level, the program
accepts external order events, persists raw deliveries, processes them through
business rules, and exposes order state, history, audit decisions, and stats.

Use this mental model only for orientation. For implementation details, always
open the focused document from the context map.

Typical flow:

1. API receives event deliveries.
2. Raw deliveries are persisted before business processing.
3. Processing jobs track technical status while the raw inbox remains immutable.
4. Processing validates, deduplicates, applies state/merge rules, and records
   decisions.
5. Reads expose the materialized order state plus history/audit/statistics.

